\pard\b\fs32 Abstract\par
\pard\fs24\b0 The rapid expansion of digital hiring ecosystems has created a large-scale data challenge in resume processing, candidate-role mapping, and recruitment analytics. This project presents a unified architecture that combines Big Data concepts with Machine Learning to deliver real-time career role prediction and ATS (Applicant Tracking System) feedback analysis. The system is designed to process resume text data, extract relevant features, classify candidate profiles, and provide actionable guidance for resume improvement.\par
\par
The machine learning core uses Natural Language Processing through TF-IDF vectorization and logistic regression with cross-validated hyperparameter tuning. The pipeline is designed for reliability, reproducibility, and extensibility. To improve class-level role understanding, domain priors are incorporated by injecting role-specific skills into training representations. This improves semantic anchoring for sparse or short resume inputs.\par
\par
The platform also includes modular APIs for health checks, model training, role prediction, and ATS scoring, allowing integration with a modern web frontend. The overall system demonstrates how scalable data architecture, interpretable machine learning, and API-based deployment can be combined for real-world, high-impact career technology applications.\par
\page

